Nigerian-American rapper King Joel has rewarded the winner of the maiden Lagos State Inter-Secondary School debate with N500,000. Agnue Dei Of Little Francis School emerged as the ultimate winner. Great Trinity College, Alakoto High School, and Body of Christ Comprehensive Secondary School emerged first and second runner-up respectively. The event with the theme: “Building a better Nigeria: The responsibility of the parents or The Government?” was held at the Teslim Balogun Stadium with six schools battling for the prize. Speaking on the debate competition, King Joel disclosed, he initiated the program having lived a better part of his life in Lagos. - Advertisement - “I saw the values attached to being educated in Nigeria and as such this prompted the need to sponsor a debate competition that would see the intending future leaders of tomorrow defend our country,” he stressed.   Ex-BBNaija’s Angel applauds self for accomplishments…     BREAKING: D’Banj, Simi join Nigerian Idol judges     Portable: I don’t take alcohol but I zazu   The project coordinator, Chiori Daniel Cole said: “It will amaze you that we were able to put smiles on the faces of over 400 vulnerable people that cut across widows we get less support, physically challenged by gifting them with food items and cash amount’. We hope to continue on these strides in years to come.” Aninneji Esther Nmasichukwu took home a cash reward of N400,000 while Ajagu Favour Onyedikachukwu got N100,000 as a cash gift from the convener The runner-up school got N200,000 while Igedi Oluwatoyin and her partner Chukwukere Esther got N100,000 each. The third-place position was a tie between Great Trinity College and Anikeola Comprehensive School. All the participants, including Obisanya Lucia, James Edinyanga, Adekanbi Wasilat and Alli Temilola get a cash prize of N100,000 each. Other competitors got N50,000 each while random kids were picked by King Joel in the crowd with a cash gift of N50,000 each.